President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his Administration. Mark Anthony Calabria of Virginia is nominated to be Director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency. Dr. Calabria currently serves as Chief Economist to Vice President Mike Pence and has previous experience in the Senate Banking Committee and the Department of Housing and Urban Development.

Heath P. Tarbert of Maryland is nominated to be Commissioner and Chairman of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission. He currently serves as Assistant Secretary for International Markets at the Treasury Department and has experience in international law and finance.

Eliot Pedrosa of Florida is nominated to be United States Executive Director of the Inter-American Development Bank. He currently represents the United States as Alternate Executive Director of the bank and has previous experience in law and public affairs.

In addition to the nominations, President Trump also announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key positions. Peter Ricketts of Nebraska is appointed to the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations, Nicholas T. Matich IV of Virginia is appointed to the Council of the Administrative Conference of the United States, and Daniel R. Sitterly of New York is appointed as Assistant Secretary of Veterans Affairs for Human Resources and Administration.